OL,6,FEarlier this month the Met revealed
OL,7,Fthat it had made 1,000 arrests using
OL,8,Flive facial recognition to date, of
OL,9,Fwhich 773 had led to charge or caution.
OL,11,FCharlie Whelton, policy and campaigns
OL,12,Fofficer at Liberty, said: "It's
OL,13,Fincredibly concerning to see an
OL,14,Fexpansion of facial recognition,
OL,15,Fespecially at a time when there is a
OL,16,Fcomplete lack of regulation governing
OL,17,Fits use.
OL,26,@tD@[OU
